-- Northwest sees second-quarter revenue decline
-- 
-- Tue Jun 12, 2007 5:37pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/12/us-northwest-revenue-idUSWEN873820070612

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Northwest Airlines Corp. NWA.N said it expects its second-quarter mainline domestic revenue per available seat mile to decline between 2 percent and 3 percent. 

 The No. 5 U.S. carrier said in a government filing that it sees its domestic consolidated revenue down 0.5 percent to 1 percent.